01:00:26.526 --> 01:00:27.726
- See you later.
- Bye-bye.

01:00:27.806 --> 01:00:28.766
Bye.

01:01:01.486 --> 01:01:04.086
But I think that Bruton Street
would be perfect for the gallery

01:01:04.166 --> 01:01:06.206
because it's just right
in the thick of things and...

01:01:06.286 --> 01:01:07.766
It'll just be a natural success,
I think,

01:01:07.846 --> 01:01:10.206
because you're great at picking out
paintings and bric-a-brac.

01:01:10.286 --> 01:01:11.526
Yeah.

01:01:11.606 --> 01:01:14.206
Knowing my luck,
I'll get pregnant the minute it opens.

01:01:14.286 --> 01:01:16.206
Yeah, well, you can manage both.
I mean...

01:01:16.286 --> 01:01:17.646
Heths didn't have a problem

01:01:17.726 --> 01:01:19.646
giving up Adair,
when we first had Rosie.

01:01:19.726 --> 01:01:21.686
Remember,
we did have a lot of help though.

01:01:21.766 --> 01:01:23.926
But the nanny left us.
She got a part in a movie.

01:01:24.006 --> 01:01:25.166
- No.
- Yeah.

01:01:25.246 --> 01:01:27.966
Actually, you know who we
bumped into the other day?

01:01:28.366 --> 01:01:30.966
- Obviously you know, but... Nola.
- Yeah.

01:01:31.006 --> 01:01:33.646
Well, I told you, we saw her.
When was it? Ages ago now.

01:01:33.726 --> 01:01:37.406
Yeah. Well, I think she's now working
in a boutique on Ledbury Road.

01:01:37.486 --> 01:01:39.606
I think it's Paul and Joe's
or something.

01:01:39.686 --> 01:01:42.046
But she's just such an odd girl.

01:01:42.086 --> 01:01:44.966
I mean, she still looks great.
Sorry, but it's true.

01:01:45.846 --> 01:01:47.846
But something's just...

01:01:47.926 --> 01:01:50.606
...changed in her face.
I mean, I... We barely spoke.

01:01:50.686 --> 01:01:52.206
Tom said she looked a bit hard.

01:01:52.286 --> 01:01:55.446
Yeah, well, she's always, you know,
been a lady of the sauce, so to speak.

01:01:55.526 --> 01:01:57.286
And I think it kind of
runs in the family,

01:01:57.366 --> 01:01:59.486
but, I don't know...

01:02:00.246 --> 01:02:02.846
I mean she's still got
that "come-hither" look.

01:02:03.606 --> 01:02:07.006
- Is she going out with anyone?
- Strangely, I forgot to ask.

01:02:07.046 --> 01:02:09.126
But I'll keep you in touch with that,
Chloe, let you know.

01:02:09.206 --> 01:02:10.446
- Hello, Tom.
- Hello.

01:02:10.526 --> 01:02:13.366
- Hello, fella.
- What are you doing here?

01:02:13.446 --> 01:02:16.286
We just popped in for a bit of,
you know, local tagliatelle.

01:02:16.326 --> 01:02:18.446
Good to see you.
What a lovely family gathering.

01:02:18.526 --> 01:02:19.886
You should have told us.
We'd have made a sextet.

01:02:19.926 --> 01:02:20.926
A sextet.
We could have had one of those.

01:02:21.006 --> 01:02:23.086
- You guys going to Hedley next month?
- Yeah, we're gonna try. Aren't we?

01:02:23.126 --> 01:02:24.486
I know Tom's dying to get away.

01:02:24.526 --> 01:02:26.126
I was yelling at you the other day.
You didn't hear me.

01:02:26.206 --> 01:02:27.206
Me?

01:02:27.286 --> 01:02:30.366
Yeah, you were hailing a cab
on Melcombe Street about, what, 5:00.

01:02:30.446 --> 01:02:33.526
- I'd have given you a lift.
- I was?

01:02:33.606 --> 01:02:35.366
- Where's Melcombe Street?
- No, not me.

01:02:35.406 --> 01:02:37.606
Yes, I mean it
certainly looked like you.

01:02:37.686 --> 01:02:40.726
- Where is Melcombe Street?
- No, I'm afraid you're mistaken.

01:02:40.806 --> 01:02:43.206
But people are always
taking me for other people. So...

01:02:43.246 --> 01:02:44.406
I'd have sworn it was you.

01:02:44.446 --> 01:02:46.606
Well, it certainly
wouldn't be Chris hailing a cab.

01:02:46.686 --> 01:02:48.566
He's completely dependant on our driver.

01:02:48.646 --> 01:02:49.886
- Quite right.
- Very annoying.

01:02:49.966 --> 01:02:53.726
You should check for early Alzheimer's.
You're forgetting. I'm sure I'm right.

01:02:53.806 --> 01:02:56.966
No, you are mistaken.
But thank you for thinking of me.

01:02:57.046 --> 01:03:00.566
I think the only thing that comes out of
this conversation is you're both nuts.

01:03:00.646 --> 01:03:03.846
- Well, you're an authority on that.
- Or drunk. How dare you?

01:03:03.926 --> 01:03:05.286
Look, we'd better be going on.
Look, call me.

01:03:05.366 --> 01:03:06.726
- I will do.
- Enjoy your supper.

01:03:06.806 --> 01:03:07.926
- Bye. See you.
- Thanks.

01:03:08.006 --> 01:03:08.966
Nuts.

01:03:10.286 --> 01:03:11.686
Good afternoon, Ingrid.

01:03:12.446 --> 01:03:14.606
Samantha, what do we have
for this afternoon?

01:03:14.686 --> 01:03:16.886
Just the Sarazin people at two.

01:03:16.966 --> 01:03:18.086
- Can we push it an hour?
- Yeah.

01:03:18.166 --> 01:03:21.406
I should be back in time, but if I'm
not, please make them comfortable.

01:03:25.486 --> 01:03:27.126
Chris. Where are you off to?

01:03:27.206 --> 01:03:29.286
I'm sorry, Rod,
I've got an appointment.

01:03:29.326 --> 01:03:31.526
We have Sarazin
and company this afternoon.

01:03:31.606 --> 01:03:34.526
I should be back in time but if I'm not,
please start without me.

01:03:34.646 --> 01:03:38.486
- Really?
- It's OK. It's important, trust me.

01:03:39.486 --> 01:03:41.326
It's ridiculous to go back to my place.

01:03:41.406 --> 01:03:43.246
Once we get there,
you'll have less than an hour.

01:03:43.326 --> 01:03:45.806
Look, it's not that I'm
miserable with Chloe, it's just...

01:03:45.846 --> 01:03:47.366
I don't wanna talk about Chloe anymore!

01:03:47.446 --> 01:03:49.566
Listen, it's just I'm bored!
I mean, she's very nice, but...

01:03:49.646 --> 01:03:51.526
- Chris!
- Are you in a bad mood?

01:03:51.606 --> 01:03:54.006
Yes, I am in a bad mood.
I just blew another audition.

01:03:54.086 --> 01:03:56.446
I'm so sick of this acting thing,
it's just not working out.

01:03:56.486 --> 01:03:57.566
It's a hard field.

01:03:57.646 --> 01:04:00.126
- You have to keep plugging at it.
- I'm sick of plugging.

01:04:00.206 --> 01:04:03.046
Tom's mother was right.
It just gets to a point, you know?

01:04:03.126 --> 01:04:04.886
Or should I say your mother-in-law?

01:04:04.926 --> 01:04:07.926
Hey, look.
Let's not go into one of those, OK?

01:04:09.126 --> 01:04:13.046
I don't know what I'm doing with you.
You're never gonna leave Chloe.

01:04:14.766 --> 01:04:16.766
Maybe I will.

01:04:18.926 --> 01:04:21.246
Don't say that unless you mean it.

01:04:22.766 --> 01:04:25.366
Chloe's just so desperate
to get pregnant.

01:04:26.126 --> 01:04:28.486
I mean, it's... mechanical.

01:04:32.686 --> 01:04:34.886
I don't know what I'd do
if I couldn't see you.

01:04:36.806 --> 01:04:39.206
Really. I mean it.

01:04:42.046 --> 01:04:44.726
- Merry bloody Christmas.
- Lovely.

01:04:44.766 --> 01:04:46.486
How many cigarettes
are you gonna smoke today?

01:04:46.566 --> 01:04:48.766
- A million, at least.
- Please don't start smoking.

01:04:48.806 --> 01:04:50.686
- Well, it is Christmas.
- It's such a pity.

01:04:50.766 --> 01:04:51.926
- Come on, just a little one.
- It's gonna...

01:04:52.006 --> 01:04:54.446
You think you're going
to be living forever, you're not.

01:04:54.646 --> 01:04:56.166
Hi.

01:04:56.246 --> 01:04:58.566
I wanted to wish you a merry Christmas.

01:04:59.726 --> 01:05:02.166
I've been thinking about you.

01:05:04.486 --> 01:05:07.886
I may be able to get away tomorrow,
for an hour or so.

01:05:09.366 --> 01:05:11.806
OK. See you then.

01:05:11.886 --> 01:05:13.446
Bye-bye.

01:05:14.126 --> 01:05:16.006
There you are, Chris.

01:05:16.086 --> 01:05:19.446
Chloe tells me you've sustained
some personal loss in the market

01:05:19.526 --> 01:05:21.286
over the past few months.

01:05:21.366 --> 01:05:24.286
Well, I guess I've been a little bit
careless, not concentrating.

01:05:24.366 --> 01:05:26.166
And, of course,
I thought I made good decisions, but...

01:05:26.246 --> 01:05:28.046
Well, who could have predicted these?

01:05:28.126 --> 01:05:30.406
Look, I don't want
you and Chloe to worry.

01:05:30.446 --> 01:05:33.326
- You'll always have a safety net.
- You're too generous, sir.

01:05:33.406 --> 01:05:34.926
Oh, no, you've made Chloe happy,

01:05:35.006 --> 01:05:37.046
and that means a great deal
to Eleanor and me.

01:06:38.246 --> 01:06:42.206
Well, I think it's gonna be
an amazing holiday. Don't you, Chris?

01:06:42.286 --> 01:06:43.646
Yes.

01:06:43.686 --> 01:06:47.406
We have a choice of sleeping
on the boat or in the different hotels.

01:06:47.486 --> 01:06:48.446
- Boat.
- Boat.

01:06:48.526 --> 01:06:49.726
- Every time.
- Good. I say the boat.

01:06:49.806 --> 01:06:51.166
Do you know he's never been
to the Greek Islands.

01:06:51.246 --> 01:06:52.486
- What?
- No.

01:06:52.566 --> 01:06:54.086
- No, he's never been.
- You'll love it.

01:06:54.166 --> 01:06:57.006
No. I have been to Athens,
but I hear the Islands are paradise.

01:06:57.086 --> 01:06:58.086
Oh, that reminds me,

01:06:58.166 --> 01:07:00.606
we have to go to Sardinia to
pop in on Brook and Dougie Winston.

01:07:00.686 --> 01:07:01.686
- Oh, good.
- Oh, God.

01:07:01.766 --> 01:07:04.286
- No, no, the house is beautiful.
- Brook's fine, Dougie's a nightmare.

01:07:04.366 --> 01:07:06.206
Sounds so romantic, doesn't it?
Mikonos and Crete.

01:07:06.246 --> 01:07:07.246
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:07:07.326 --> 01:07:09.846
I'm so anxious to see all the
beautiful old temples and theaters.

01:07:09.926 --> 01:07:10.926
Oh, God.

01:07:11.006 --> 01:07:12.446
Yeah. Oh, I'll do that with you.
Tom can stay...

01:07:12.486 --> 01:07:15.486
You know, I bought Chris
an ancient Greek fertility charm.

01:07:15.526 --> 01:07:17.406
- Do you remember?
- I'll never forget.

01:07:17.486 --> 01:07:19.166
I sent off for that fertility thingy.

01:07:19.246 --> 01:07:22.166
He had to put it under
his pillow for two months.

01:07:22.246 --> 01:07:25.246
And absolutely nothing happened,
of course.

01:07:25.326 --> 01:07:26.286
Poor thing.

01:07:26.366 --> 01:07:28.966
- I'd just subjected him to the torture.
- They think he's firing blanks.

01:07:29.046 --> 01:07:30.046
- Oh, shut up!
- Hello?

01:07:30.126 --> 01:07:31.806
I miss you.

01:07:32.366 --> 01:07:34.606
- Love me. Just love me.
- No, because it's not funny.

01:07:34.686 --> 01:07:36.166
- It's not funny.
- I'm sorry.

01:07:36.206 --> 01:07:38.366
Proof is in the pudding,
and there ain't been any pudding.

01:07:38.446 --> 01:07:40.526
- I can't get away right now.
- Well, you have to.

01:07:40.606 --> 01:07:42.206
When can you get here?

01:07:43.406 --> 01:07:45.646
Tomorrow. No, Monday.

01:07:45.686 --> 01:07:47.046
Look...

01:07:47.726 --> 01:07:49.446
It's a three-day weekend.

01:07:49.726 --> 01:07:51.286
Tuesday.

01:07:51.846 --> 01:07:53.846
Chris, I need to see you.

01:07:55.006 --> 01:07:57.686
I'll see what I can do.
I'll call you right back.

01:07:57.766 --> 01:08:00.206
I would love to meet Barbra Streisand.

01:08:00.286 --> 01:08:03.246
She's meant to be really lovely.
She's with that other American fella.

01:08:03.326 --> 01:08:04.886
- Who was that?
- Oh, I'm such an idiot.

01:08:04.966 --> 01:08:07.366
I forgot to sign some papers.
I may have to drive into town.

01:08:07.406 --> 01:08:08.406
Jack Garner?

01:08:08.486 --> 01:08:10.526
You can't go,
it's a bank holiday weekend.

01:08:10.606 --> 01:08:11.886
The traffic'll be terrible.

01:08:11.966 --> 01:08:14.366
- James Garner, that's it.
- I mean, we've all got plans.

01:08:14.446 --> 01:08:15.406
I don't mean today.

01:08:15.486 --> 01:08:17.166
They named their little dog
after Elaine Paige.

01:08:17.246 --> 01:08:18.566
Well, surely it can wait
a couple of days.

01:08:18.645 --> 01:08:20.446
- Why did they do that?
- 'Cause it howls all night long.

01:08:20.526 --> 01:08:22.046
- Yes, I'm sure it can.
- Oh, that's mean.

01:08:22.126 --> 01:08:23.886
I know. And it's
terribly small and furry.

01:08:23.966 --> 01:08:24.966
That's mean.

01:08:25.526 --> 01:08:28.046
I think tomorrow
we should go for a morning ride.

01:08:28.126 --> 01:08:29.606
I've some lovely new horses.

01:08:29.685 --> 01:08:31.286
Do you remember when
Chris came here first,

01:08:31.326 --> 01:08:33.326
and he had some
serious qualms about riding?

01:08:33.366 --> 01:08:34.486
- I spoke to Teddy.
- How is he?

01:08:34.566 --> 01:08:36.366
Well, this morning he was talking
about buying a horse of his own.

01:08:36.446 --> 01:08:38.046
- No.
- Yeah.

01:08:38.126 --> 01:08:39.645
I don't know, it was all in good fun.

01:08:39.725 --> 01:08:40.845
- Where from?
- Anyway...

01:08:40.926 --> 01:08:43.326
- I think Nan's got a really nice mare.
...he's a wonderful new horse.

01:08:43.406 --> 01:08:46.206
Telephone call, sir.
She said it was important.

01:08:49.286 --> 01:08:50.805
Excuse me.

01:08:52.126 --> 01:08:54.126
- Tomorrow morning?
- Do you wanna come?

01:08:54.206 --> 01:08:56.886
That bloody phone
has not stopped ringing all weekend.

01:08:56.966 --> 01:08:59.006
- I know.
- It's so irritating.

01:08:59.446 --> 01:09:00.446
Hello?

01:09:00.526 --> 01:09:02.685
I tried to call your mobile,
but it's off.

01:09:03.166 --> 01:09:05.126
Are you mad calling me here?

01:09:05.725 --> 01:09:07.366
When are you coming over?

01:09:07.446 --> 01:09:09.446
I'm trying to make it for tomorrow.

01:09:09.526 --> 01:09:11.606
I can't wait till tomorrow,
I'm going crazy.

01:09:11.685 --> 01:09:14.526
- What the hell's the matter?
- I'm pregnant.

01:09:20.685 --> 01:09:22.685
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

01:09:22.765 --> 01:09:25.246
'Cause we've got to go
and try and look at this...

01:09:25.286 --> 01:09:28.406
...horse for Chris.
- They got it in the navy?

01:09:29.166 --> 01:09:32.086
Yeah, the... It was lack of enough
vegetables, or something.

01:09:32.166 --> 01:09:34.685
I wonder if that's why they took
lemons and oranges...

01:09:34.765 --> 01:09:36.086
Well, they only had biscuits.

01:09:36.166 --> 01:09:38.526
Well, that's where
Rose's Lime Cordial originated...

01:09:38.606 --> 01:09:42.366
- Who keeps calling?
- It was Samantha, my secretary.

01:09:42.446 --> 01:09:45.566
I'm afraid I won't be able
to go riding tomorrow. I can't help it.

01:09:45.645 --> 01:09:47.926
I thought Samantha said she was
going to her parents this weekend.

01:09:48.006 --> 01:09:50.246
I know, it's all my fault. Poor girl.

01:09:51.166 --> 01:09:52.486
It's no big deal.

01:09:52.566 --> 01:09:53.725
I'll pop back into town.

01:09:53.845 --> 01:09:57.806
The whole thing'll take a few hours,
and it'll be off my mind. I promise.

01:09:57.886 --> 01:09:59.566
- That's a shame.
- It's really sad.

01:09:59.646 --> 01:10:01.246
Well, it is a pity because I...

01:10:01.326 --> 01:10:03.526
I think it's unfair
on Samantha too, frankly.

01:10:03.606 --> 01:10:04.966
Yeah. Well, it's unfortunate,

01:10:05.046 --> 01:10:07.166
but, you know,
Chris has a lot of responsibility.

01:10:07.246 --> 01:10:08.886
Well, anyway,
let's not worry about it. Let's...

01:10:08.966 --> 01:10:10.446
- Slave driver.
- Look, as long as we make lamb bone.

01:10:10.526 --> 01:10:11.526
- Can you, can you?
- Well, I think so.

01:10:11.606 --> 01:10:11.686
- How the hell did you get pregnant?
- I told you that weekend last month

01:10:11.686 --> 01:10:14.366
- How the hell did you get pregnant?
- I told you that weekend last month

01:10:14.446 --> 01:10:16.246
that we needed to be careful
and I didn't have protection,

01:10:16.326 --> 01:10:17.886
but you couldn't wait.

01:10:19.806 --> 01:10:21.686
What unbelievable bad luck.

01:10:21.766 --> 01:10:24.566
Christ, I can't get my wife pregnant
no matter how hard I try,

01:10:24.606 --> 01:10:26.446
and the minute you're unprotected
I knock you up.

01:10:26.526 --> 01:10:28.326
It's 'cause you love me,
and you don't love her.

01:10:28.406 --> 01:10:29.406
Is that your interpretation?

01:10:29.486 --> 01:10:31.566
It's a child conceived
out of genuine passion,

01:10:31.646 --> 01:10:34.206
not as part of some fertility project.

01:10:34.286 --> 01:10:36.206
OK. Well I'll go with you,
and we'll get it sorted.

01:10:36.286 --> 01:10:38.046
- I'm not doing that again.
- Again?

01:10:38.086 --> 01:10:40.646
- What's that supposed to mean?
- It's the third time.

01:10:40.726 --> 01:10:43.246
I did it once when I was younger,
and then I did it for Tom.

01:10:43.326 --> 01:10:45.126
I didn't want to, but he insisted.

01:10:45.206 --> 01:10:47.166
Nola, I really can't see any other way.

01:10:47.246 --> 01:10:49.246
- Why can't I just have it?
- And what?

01:10:49.326 --> 01:10:52.246
- And we'll raise it together.
- That's obviously not possible.

01:10:52.326 --> 01:10:54.286
Why? You hate your job,
you hate your life.

01:10:54.366 --> 01:10:57.046
I mean, it seems like a blessing.
It's a sign.

01:10:57.126 --> 01:10:58.806
Look, Nola, I have to go.

01:10:58.886 --> 01:11:00.846
I'm juggling six things
at the same time

01:11:00.926 --> 01:11:03.486
just to make
this trip to the city look legit.

01:11:05.086 --> 01:11:06.446
I'll talk to you on Tuesday.

01:11:06.526 --> 01:11:07.766
Chris...

01:11:07.846 --> 01:11:10.966
You must... I expect you
to do the right thing, OK?

01:11:11.046 --> 01:11:13.566
I'm not walking away from this.

01:11:15.206 --> 01:11:18.166
Is anything the matter?
You seemed very gloomy all weekend.

01:11:20.486 --> 01:11:23.606
- I wanted to talk to you.
- What about?

01:11:24.606 --> 01:11:26.726
Us.

01:11:27.206 --> 01:11:29.166
Is something wrong?

01:11:31.086 --> 01:11:33.406
Yeah. There is.

01:11:34.886 --> 01:11:35.886
What?

01:11:35.966 --> 01:11:39.006
If you're still taking a hammering
financially in the market,

01:11:39.086 --> 01:11:40.566
you know it's not a problem.

01:11:41.086 --> 01:11:43.766
I can't keep leaning
on your father, Chloe.

01:11:44.886 --> 01:11:48.166
Papa gets more pleasure
out of helping his family,

01:11:48.246 --> 01:11:51.766
than all the possessions he owns.
You know that.

01:11:54.766 --> 01:11:56.526
What is it?

01:12:01.046 --> 01:12:04.406
Is it something to do
with those phone calls you kept getting?

01:12:05.526 --> 01:12:08.766
Because you acted
really strangely after each of them.

01:12:13.126 --> 01:12:15.526
Are you having an affair?

01:12:16.486 --> 01:12:18.726
Am I having an affair?

01:12:18.806 --> 01:12:20.886
Yeah, that's what I asked.

01:12:22.926 --> 01:12:25.286
- No.
- You are.

01:12:25.326 --> 01:12:27.526
Of course I'm not. Don't be silly.

01:12:38.326 --> 01:12:40.846
Do you not love me anymore?

01:12:43.046 --> 01:12:45.246
Of course I love you.

01:12:46.486 --> 01:12:48.646
Well, what's wrong?

01:12:51.846 --> 01:12:54.086
I just feel like I'm letting you down.

01:12:54.126 --> 01:12:56.166
You're not. How?

01:12:59.166 --> 01:13:01.806
Is it because I'm not getting pregnant?

01:13:05.126 --> 01:13:07.126
I just...

01:13:07.766 --> 01:13:10.166
...feel so guilty.

01:13:10.966 --> 01:13:13.686
So terribly guilty.

01:13:13.766 --> 01:13:16.086
Listen, Chris.

01:13:16.166 --> 01:13:19.606
We've both been to the doctor.
We're both perfectly healthy.

01:13:19.686 --> 01:13:24.126
I can conceive and you're perfectly
capable of making a woman pregnant.

01:13:25.806 --> 01:13:30.086
Is it me? Have I been horribly pushy
and obnoxious on the subject?

01:13:30.966 --> 01:13:35.806
Look, I... I just want a baby.
I want to have our baby.

01:13:37.766 --> 01:13:40.486
We haven't been lucky yet, that's all.

01:13:44.086 --> 01:13:45.646
Oh, Chloe.

01:13:51.606 --> 01:13:53.846
Let's get off the subject.

01:13:53.886 --> 01:13:57.886
Having a child should be something
that makes us both happy and excited,

01:13:57.966 --> 01:14:01.726
not a cause of all this
tension and anxiety and...

01:14:05.366 --> 01:14:07.366
I had to talk to somebody.

01:14:08.646 --> 01:14:10.006
I'm really suffering.

01:14:10.086 --> 01:14:13.166
Whatever you tell me goes no further.

01:14:14.406 --> 01:14:17.406
I'm contemplating leaving my wife
for another woman.

01:14:18.806 --> 01:14:20.766
But when the time came to tell her...

01:14:21.806 --> 01:14:23.406
...I couldn't do it.

01:14:23.486 --> 01:14:25.966
Yeah, well, it's not the easiest
thing in the world to do, is it?

01:14:28.126 --> 01:14:29.806
It's crazy.

01:14:31.086 --> 01:14:33.806
I can see no real future
with this other woman.

01:14:33.966 --> 01:14:36.246
And I have a very
comfortable life with my wife.

01:14:36.326 --> 01:14:39.646
- Yeah, but if you don't love her...
- I'm not saying I don't love her.

01:14:39.726 --> 01:14:42.326
Just not in the way I feel
about this other woman.

01:14:42.366 --> 01:14:44.086
Right.

01:14:44.806 --> 01:14:47.966
Maybe it's finally the difference
between love and lust.

01:14:48.086 --> 01:14:50.566
But what the hell
am I going to do if I leave Chloe?

01:14:52.846 --> 01:14:56.486
I don't fool myself that I haven't
gotten used to a certain kind of living.

01:14:56.566 --> 01:14:59.966
Am I supposed to give it all up?
For what?

01:15:00.646 --> 01:15:02.206
Is it for a woman you love?

01:15:02.286 --> 01:15:05.006
To live how? Where?

01:15:05.286 --> 01:15:08.286
- To work as what?
- Well, it seems to me that you...

01:15:08.326 --> 01:15:10.246
You're pretty good
at what you're doing.

01:15:10.326 --> 01:15:13.406
There must be another job in another
firm that you can just, you know...

01:15:13.486 --> 01:15:16.526
Let's face it,
I'm the boss's son-in-law.

01:15:16.606 --> 01:15:18.726
And he loves me.

01:15:19.846 --> 01:15:22.326
Doesn't seem to me like you
want this other woman enough

01:15:22.406 --> 01:15:24.966
to give up everything
you've achieved for it.

01:15:25.606 --> 01:15:27.846
We're going away for three weeks.

01:15:27.926 --> 01:15:30.966
- When I get back I'll tell her.
- When you get back?

01:15:32.006 --> 01:15:34.446
What am I supposed to do?
Stop playing games with me!

01:15:34.486 --> 01:15:37.806
- I'm not playing games with you.
- Why don't you just tell her now then?

01:15:37.886 --> 01:15:40.046
I'd think you'd want
to stop living such a sham.

01:15:40.126 --> 01:15:43.126
- Look, it's not easy.
- Why not?

01:15:43.166 --> 01:15:46.206
If you're so bored at home with her
and you're so crazy about me,

01:15:46.286 --> 01:15:47.686
which is all you ever tell me...

01:15:47.766 --> 01:15:50.526
I don't wanna mess
this holiday up for everybody, OK?

01:15:51.806 --> 01:15:53.806
It's a big blow.

01:15:53.846 --> 01:15:56.006
And it's gonna make
a huge impact on everyone.

01:15:56.086 --> 01:15:59.446
How can you go on vacation with a
woman that you know you're gonna leave

01:15:59.526 --> 01:16:01.606
- the minute you get back?
- Keep your voice down.

01:16:01.686 --> 01:16:04.286
You wanna know how I feel?
I'm jealous, OK?

01:16:04.366 --> 01:16:06.446
I don't like the idea
of you making love with her.

01:16:06.526 --> 01:16:10.766
I don't like the idea of you going off
island-hopping with her. It's romantic!

01:16:10.846 --> 01:16:12.846
Hey, keep your voice down.

01:16:13.846 --> 01:16:16.086
You know I make love to her.

01:16:16.126 --> 01:16:18.646
And you know it's just routine.

01:16:19.366 --> 01:16:22.126
For God's sakes,
can't you wait a few weeks?

01:16:24.526 --> 01:16:26.126
Yeah.

01:16:27.446 --> 01:16:30.286
I just wanna know that
something's gonna happen, you know?

01:16:30.366 --> 01:16:32.006
It will.

01:16:33.366 --> 01:16:35.566
- It will.
- OK.

01:16:40.246 --> 01:16:42.006
The holiday's off.

01:16:42.086 --> 01:16:43.526
Why? What happened?

01:16:43.606 --> 01:16:45.766
Maurice Lewis has
to go in for an operation.

01:16:46.766 --> 01:16:48.006
Why?

01:16:48.086 --> 01:16:50.486
Disc in his back or something.
He can't walk.

01:16:50.526 --> 01:16:52.326
Anyway, he needs recovery time

01:16:52.406 --> 01:16:55.646
and everyone thought we should
just move it till after the summer.

01:16:55.726 --> 01:16:57.166
Let me just pack up my stuff.

01:16:57.246 --> 01:16:59.806
We should probably walk to the opera,
it's so close.

01:16:59.886 --> 01:17:01.566
Yeah.

01:17:17.606 --> 01:17:18.646
Hello?

01:17:31.646 --> 01:17:33.646
Hello?

01:17:49.846 --> 01:17:51.686
An opportunity has arisen, Chris,

01:17:51.726 --> 01:17:53.726
which I think may be
a lucrative one for you.

01:17:53.806 --> 01:17:54.806
Really?

01:17:54.886 --> 01:17:56.886
We're structuring something
with a Japanese company.

01:17:56.966 --> 01:18:00.086
It's an independent operation. There's
a great deal of money to be made.

01:18:00.206 --> 01:18:04.566
And my thought was, anyone in on the
ground floor stands to profit hugely,

01:18:04.646 --> 01:18:06.886
assuming our predictions are correct.

01:18:06.966 --> 01:18:08.366
- Sounds exciting.
- It is.

01:18:08.406 --> 01:18:11.406
Eleanor. I've just
told Chris the good news.

01:18:11.486 --> 01:18:14.406
But what would make me the happiest
has nothing to do with money.

01:18:14.446 --> 01:18:16.526
I'd like you to make me
a young grandmother.

01:18:16.606 --> 01:18:18.606
You already are a young grandmother.

01:18:18.646 --> 01:18:20.926
Yes. Tom and Heather
are trying for their second,

01:18:21.006 --> 01:18:23.006
but I'd like you to be a mother.

01:18:23.086 --> 01:18:25.286
Oh, all right.
Don't look at me like that.

01:18:25.366 --> 01:18:28.526
I'll be quiet. What would you
like for your birthday?

01:18:28.606 --> 01:18:30.326
- I don't know.
- Your birthday?

01:18:30.406 --> 01:18:32.366
Great. You forgot.

01:18:32.446 --> 01:18:35.086
I didn't actually.
I bought you something already.

01:18:35.166 --> 01:18:36.846
So my hints worked.

01:18:37.926 --> 01:18:40.006
- Mummy...
- I knew. I knew.

01:18:40.086 --> 01:18:41.086
- We are trying. We don't want to...
- All right.

01:18:41.166 --> 01:18:43.406
- Hello?
- Chris?

01:18:43.486 --> 01:18:44.726
- Excuse me.
- By all means.

01:18:44.806 --> 01:18:46.286
- I weigh as much as I did.
- Yes, darling.

01:18:46.366 --> 01:18:47.966
- Look, please relax, OK?
- I spoke out of turn.

01:18:48.046 --> 01:18:49.606
- Hey. Hey.
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:18:49.726 --> 01:18:51.006
- What are you two bickering about?
- Nothing.

01:18:51.046 --> 01:18:53.326
I told you not to call me, I'd call you.

01:18:53.486 --> 01:18:55.966
Well, I... I...
I was waiting for you to call.

01:18:56.046 --> 01:18:57.366
I've been waiting a week.

01:18:57.566 --> 01:19:00.326
Well, there's always
people around and I can't talk.

01:19:00.806 --> 01:19:02.446
When are you coming home?

01:19:02.606 --> 01:19:04.006
In about two weeks.

01:19:04.086 --> 01:19:06.726
About two weeks? You said
the whole trip was three weeks!

01:19:06.806 --> 01:19:08.166
Yeah, right. Three weeks.

01:19:08.246 --> 01:19:10.046
Chris, Mummy and Papa are leaving.

01:19:10.126 --> 01:19:12.006
OK. OK...

01:19:12.166 --> 01:19:13.926
Who is that? What country are you in?

01:19:14.006 --> 01:19:16.046
Your mobile's been impossible.

01:19:16.406 --> 01:19:18.566
I told you. I'm in Greece.

01:19:18.606 --> 01:19:21.086
And there's always people around,
so I can't talk.

01:19:21.166 --> 01:19:23.766
I said I'd be home soon,
and I will call you.

01:19:24.606 --> 01:19:26.766
I'm just lonely. I'm anxious.

01:19:26.846 --> 01:19:28.246
Can you just?

01:19:28.766 --> 01:19:30.886
Please tell Chloe
as soon as you get home.

01:19:30.966 --> 01:19:33.686
I just want this situation
to be resolved.

01:19:34.246 --> 01:19:36.046
Do you miss me?

01:19:36.126 --> 01:19:38.086
OK. Bye, bye.

01:19:39.126 --> 01:19:41.366
- Is everything OK?
- Yeah, everything's fine.

01:19:41.446 --> 01:19:43.166
- Are you leaving already?
- Yeah.

01:20:09.766 --> 01:20:12.486
Chris, it's Nola.
Where have I reached you?

01:20:12.966 --> 01:20:14.486
Sardinia.

01:20:14.566 --> 01:20:16.846
I'll be back in five or six days, OK?

01:20:27.526 --> 01:20:29.806
- Good morning, John.
- Oh, you're early, sir.

01:20:29.846 --> 01:20:31.646
- I'll bring the car around.
- Yes.

01:20:37.926 --> 01:20:39.006
You lied to me.

01:20:39.086 --> 01:20:40.646
- Oh, Jesus.
- You lied to me!

01:20:40.726 --> 01:20:42.206
- Quiet!
- I wanna see Chloe!

01:20:42.286 --> 01:20:44.046
- Quiet, quiet.
- I wanna talk to Chloe.

01:20:44.126 --> 01:20:45.086
Look, Christ, Christ.

01:20:45.166 --> 01:20:46.366
No, no, no, listen.
Listen, I can explain.

01:20:46.446 --> 01:20:47.686
I wanna talk to Chloe.
You're a liar! You're a liar!

01:20:47.766 --> 01:20:48.926
I can explain. I... Taxi!

01:20:48.966 --> 01:20:50.326
- I'm not going anywhere with you.
- Taxi!

01:20:50.366 --> 01:20:52.606
- I'm not going anywhere with you.
- Calm down.

01:20:52.686 --> 01:20:55.526
- Nola! Nola, calm down. Calm down.
- You're a liar! You're a liar!

01:20:55.606 --> 01:20:57.086
I came home deliberately,
I came home early.

01:20:57.166 --> 01:20:59.646
You're a liar! I wanna talk to Chloe.

01:20:59.726 --> 01:21:02.326
- I wanna talk to Chloe!
- Calm down. Calm the fuck down!

01:21:02.406 --> 01:21:06.246
I wanna talk to Chloe.
You liar! You're a liar!

01:21:06.846 --> 01:21:08.246
You're a liar!

01:21:12.166 --> 01:21:15.126
I decided to cut the trip short
because all this is eating away at me.

01:21:15.206 --> 01:21:17.006
I only came back
the day before yesterday

01:21:17.086 --> 01:21:19.246
because I need a week
in the city to deal with Chloe

01:21:19.326 --> 01:21:22.126
- without you breathing down my neck.
- You're driving me crazy!

01:21:22.206 --> 01:21:24.166
I don't know whether
to believe you or not.

01:21:24.206 --> 01:21:26.006
- Please believe me, Nola.
- Well, did you tell her?

01:21:26.086 --> 01:21:27.406
I was about to when you called.

01:21:27.486 --> 01:21:28.526
What does that have to do with anything?

01:21:28.606 --> 01:21:29.766
- I got flustered.
- Oh, please!

01:21:29.846 --> 01:21:31.366
I was all set to tell her
and then you called,

01:21:31.446 --> 01:21:33.486
and then I feel guilty about
telling you that I'm still in Greece.

01:21:33.566 --> 01:21:36.206
- You said Sardinia.
- I... I was talking fast.

01:21:36.286 --> 01:21:38.726
I... I didn't want her to know
what I was talking about.

01:21:38.806 --> 01:21:40.406
Well, she has to know eventually.

01:21:40.726 --> 01:21:42.686
- I can't tell her.
- Then I will.

01:21:42.766 --> 01:21:43.766
Nola, stop!

01:21:43.846 --> 01:21:46.086
Well, this is crazy.
We're having a child together!

01:21:46.166 --> 01:21:47.726
We don't have to have a child together.

01:21:47.806 --> 01:21:49.566
It would make life
a hell of a lot simpler if we didn't.

01:21:49.646 --> 01:21:51.686
Yeah, simpler for you, but not for me.

01:21:52.766 --> 01:21:55.046
It occurred to me
that even if you had the child,

01:21:55.126 --> 01:21:57.766
- I could help you out financially.
- That's not enough.

01:21:57.846 --> 01:21:59.766
Nola, be reasonable.

01:21:59.846 --> 01:22:02.846
That's exactly what Tom said
when he broke off our engagement.

01:22:02.926 --> 01:22:05.086
Being reasonable
got me where I am right now.

01:22:05.166 --> 01:22:06.486
So, you're threatening me?

01:22:06.566 --> 01:22:09.166
If I don't do what you say,
you're gonna go to my wife.

01:22:09.486 --> 01:22:11.086
Were you lying to me?

01:22:11.246 --> 01:22:12.646
All those times we made love,

01:22:12.726 --> 01:22:15.726
all those conversations,
were you lying to me then?

01:22:15.806 --> 01:22:18.326
- Of course I wasn't lying.
- Tell Chloe.

01:22:18.406 --> 01:22:22.246
Someone has to explain the situation.
Either you do it, or I'll do it.

01:22:23.326 --> 01:22:26.966
OK, OK. I'll do the right thing.

01:24:22.086 --> 01:24:23.446
Have you seen Chris?

01:24:23.526 --> 01:24:25.526
A minute ago. He went that way.

01:24:25.966 --> 01:24:27.646
Chris?

01:24:28.446 --> 01:24:29.606
Chris?

01:24:30.766 --> 01:24:32.566
Chris?

01:24:40.006 --> 01:24:42.126
Where are you, Chris?

01:24:43.406 --> 01:24:45.406
Chris?

01:24:48.406 --> 01:24:51.206
Chloe, are you there?

01:24:51.286 --> 01:24:52.766
Have you seen Chris anywhere?

01:24:52.806 --> 01:24:55.126
No. Could you come up for a minute?

01:24:55.206 --> 01:24:57.806
I want you to give me
some advice about this dress.

01:24:58.446 --> 01:25:00.406
Yeah, OK.

01:25:25.926 --> 01:25:27.926
I'm telling Chloe tomorrow.

01:25:28.006 --> 01:25:30.726
You say that every day,
and you always back out.

01:25:30.806 --> 01:25:33.806
I'm back where I started.
I want something done, Chris.

01:25:33.886 --> 01:25:35.886
If you don't have
the nerve to do it, I'll do it.

01:25:35.966 --> 01:25:38.846
That would be revenge for you against
the whole Hewett family, wouldn't it?

01:25:38.886 --> 01:25:40.926
What the hell is that supposed to mean?

01:25:41.006 --> 01:25:43.766
My theory is you want me to tell Chloe
so you don't have to do it yourself.

01:25:43.846 --> 01:25:46.566
My God, it seems like you've
had this whole thing checked out

01:25:46.646 --> 01:25:48.166
- by some psychiatrist.
- I wish.

01:25:48.246 --> 01:25:51.326
I wish had someone to confide in,
but it's all so damn secretive.

01:25:51.406 --> 01:25:53.886
Look, Chris,
if I don't do something about this,

01:25:53.966 --> 01:25:56.006
we're gonna grow apart.
I'm having your child!

01:25:56.086 --> 01:25:58.606
I'm telling her tomorrow, Nola.
What more do you want me to do?

01:25:58.686 --> 01:26:00.766
What more? Tell her now!
Tell her tonight!

01:26:00.846 --> 01:26:04.126
I can't, not before she goes to sleep.
It wouldn't be the right time.

01:26:04.526 --> 01:26:06.166
Nola, tomorrow is fine.

01:26:06.246 --> 01:26:10.446
- What time will you get back from work?
- Same time I always get off, 6:30.

01:26:10.526 --> 01:26:12.046
So you'll be home by a quarter to seven?

01:26:12.086 --> 01:26:15.646
Yeah. Chris, you make me say
these things. I hate myself for them.

01:26:15.766 --> 01:26:17.926
- I just want us to be together.
- We will be.

01:26:19.886 --> 01:26:22.406
You were very nervy
all through the ballet.

01:26:22.486 --> 01:26:23.686
Did you hate it?

01:26:23.766 --> 01:26:26.406
- No, I'm just out of sorts.
- Yeah.

01:26:26.486 --> 01:26:28.366
I thought you were gonna pass out.

01:26:28.406 --> 01:26:30.726
Low blood sugar. I'll be better soon.

01:26:33.686 --> 01:26:36.006
I still can't do it with you tonight.

01:26:36.046 --> 01:26:38.486
I'm not over my little dose of whatever.

01:26:42.526 --> 01:26:45.726
Did the cleaner put one of my
tennis shirts in with your gear?

01:26:45.806 --> 01:26:46.926
No. What are you doing?

01:26:47.006 --> 01:26:48.686
Really? Just let me have a quick look.

01:26:48.726 --> 01:26:50.686
- I can't find it anywhere.
- No. Look, I'll check, I'll check.

01:26:50.726 --> 01:26:54.606
- I've got everything arranged in there.
- OK. I wasn't gonna disturb anything.

01:26:54.686 --> 01:26:56.406
'Cause I don't know
where else it can be.

01:26:56.486 --> 01:26:59.326
She's always bloody
mixing my stuff in with yours.

01:27:03.446 --> 01:27:04.446
Is this it?

01:27:04.526 --> 01:27:07.086
See, I knew it!
She always bloody does that.

01:27:07.166 --> 01:27:09.086
I've got to have words
with her about it.

01:27:09.166 --> 01:27:10.766
It's really...

01:27:10.846 --> 01:27:12.566
What did you just put in your pocket?

01:27:12.646 --> 01:27:15.246
- Oh, it's just my pill box.
- What do you mean a pill box?

01:27:15.326 --> 01:27:16.686
A pill box. You know
what a pill box looks like.

01:27:16.766 --> 01:27:18.446
Let me have a look at it.
What pills are you taking?

01:27:18.526 --> 01:27:20.086
No, they're just my pills. I need them.

01:27:20.166 --> 01:27:22.766
No, no, no, it's for stress,
'cause you stress me so much.

01:27:22.846 --> 01:27:24.046
- Guess what?
- What?

01:27:24.126 --> 01:27:26.526
I got tickets for the theater
for tomorrow night.

01:27:26.566 --> 01:27:28.566
You haven't. That's not like you.

01:27:28.646 --> 01:27:30.886
- What for?
- The Woman in White.

01:27:30.966 --> 01:27:33.766
- I heard it's great.
- I thought you hated musicals.

01:27:33.846 --> 01:27:35.566
No, that's not so.

01:27:35.606 --> 01:27:39.086
- And anyway, you love his music.
- Well, that's great.

01:27:39.166 --> 01:27:41.086
I'll have to meet you
outside the theater,

01:27:41.166 --> 01:27:43.526
'cause I'll be coming
straight from the gallery.

01:27:43.606 --> 01:27:45.326
Why don't you take the chauffeur?

01:27:45.406 --> 01:27:49.006
I'll grab a taxi, and with any luck
I can get an hour of tennis in.

01:27:49.926 --> 01:27:52.046
You're so sweet.

01:27:52.126 --> 01:27:54.606
You knew how much
I wanted to see that.

01:27:57.646 --> 01:28:00.446
All right, come to bed,
because you're tired, my darling.

01:28:00.526 --> 01:28:02.326
OK, I will.

01:28:05.286 --> 01:28:07.966
- Hello?
- Hello, Nola?

01:28:09.286 --> 01:28:11.486
When you get off work today,
come right home.

01:28:11.566 --> 01:28:13.566
I have some good news.

01:28:14.806 --> 01:28:18.006
Everything's taken care of,
but I'm reluctant to talk on the phone.

01:28:18.086 --> 01:28:19.966
You've got to meet me
right after work.

01:28:20.046 --> 01:28:22.726
We have... plans to make.

01:28:23.686 --> 01:28:27.006
OK. I'll cancel my agent appointment.

01:28:27.086 --> 01:28:28.806
It's good. This is good.

